CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 15, 1947, pg. 9, reads: "Elaborate Nuptials - Elaborate nuptials united Miss Carrie Beatrice, daughter of Mrs. Edward Beailey [Bailey] of Homestead and James Brooks, son of Mr. and Mrs. James Brooks Sr., recently. Included in the bridal party were Rose Fairifay, Walter Cain, Dorothy Carpenter, Mildred White, the bride and groom, Charles Smith, Estelle Gordon, Alexander Broodwar, Gertrude Dixon, Joseph Robinson, Maureen Gordon, niece of the bride, was flower girl, and Franklin Jenkins Jr. was the ring bearer. The Rev. J. J. Morton of Second Baptist Church officiated. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom James Brooks and bride Carrie Beatrice Bailey surrounded by wedding party including Rose Fairifay, Walter Cain, Dorothy Carpenter, Mildred White, Charles Smith, Estelle Gordon, Alexander Broodwar, Gertrude Dixon, Joseph Robinson, flower girl Maureen Gordon, and ring bearer Franklin Jenkins Jr., posed in Second Baptist Church, Homestead
